Movie producer Femi Adebayo has been in a celebratory mood following the massive success of his latest project “King of Thieves” (Agesinkole). The star actor, who has continued to receive accolades for the originality of the story and costume in his self-produced movie, shared a video where he was seen dancing energetically. Captioning the post, Adebayo revealed ‘King of Thieves’ has grossed over N224 million in just four weeks, placing it among the top 10 highest-grossing movie in Nigeria. He appreciated all and sundry for the overwhelming acceptance of his movie. “When you hear #KingOfThieves does 224m+ in 4weeks!”   My new body every man’s choice, Eniola Badmus gushes     I’ve never said ‘I love you’ to any lady…     How I was spiritually attacked, by Chinwetalu Agu   “You all made this happen.. Thank you for showing #KingOfThievesMovie so much love… Thank you”, he wrote. “King of Thieves”, released on April 4, 2022 is an epic tale of ‘Agesinkole’, an all-powerful bandit and his reign of terror in the prosperous Kingdom of Ajeromi. According to the ace actor, the epic action-thriller was to showcase the creativity of the Yoruba culture to the entire world and announce the crop of talents existent in the Yoruba genre. “King of Thieves” features Toyin Abraham, Lateef Adedimeji, Adebayo Salami, Broda Shagi, Femi Adebayo, Segun Arinze, among other A-list actors.